paragraphs.title: Reading meetup and meetup_tags to DataFrames
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.pyspark

import json 

catalog_meetup_tags = json.dumps({"table": {"namespace": "default", "name": "meetup_tags"},
  "rowkey": "key",
  "columns":
  {"key": {"cf": "rowkey", "col": "key", "type": "string"},
   "meetup_key": {"cf": "cf", "col": "meetup_key", "type": "string"},
   "class": {"cf": "cf", "col": "class", "type": "string"},
   "score": {"cf": "cf", "col": "score", "type": "float"},
   "x1": {"cf": "cf", "col": "x1", "type": "int"},
   "y1": {"cf": "cf", "col": "y1", "type": "int"},
   "x2": {"cf": "cf", "col": "x2", "type": "int"},
   "y2": {"cf": "cf", "col": "y2", "type": "int"}
   }})
   
catalog_meetup = json.dumps({"table": {"namespace": "default", "name": "meetup"},
  "rowkey": "key",
  "columns":
  {"key": {"cf": "rowkey", "col": "key", "type": "string"},
   "source": {"cf": "cf", "col": "source", "type": "string"},
   "user": {"cf": "cf", "col": "user", "type": "string"},
   "message": {"cf": "cf", "col": "message", "type": "string"},
   "original_image": {"cf": "cf", "col": "original_image", "type": "binary"},
   "result_image": {"cf": "cf", "col": "result_image", "type": "binary"}
   }})
                               
   
meetup_tags = sqlContext.read.format("org.apache.spark.sql.execution.datasources.hbase").option("catalog",catalog_meetup_tags).load()
meetup = sqlContext.read.format("org.apache.spark.sql.execution.datasources.hbase").option("catalog",catalog_meetup).load()

paragraphs.title: Elephant Word Cloud !
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.pyspark

from os import path
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from PIL import Image
from wordcloud import WordCloud, STOPWORDS 

text_list = meetup_tags.select('class').collect()
text = ' '.join(e[0] for e in text_list)
text = text * 3

file = open("/home/zeppelin/more.txt", "r") 
text = text + file.read()

emask = np.array(Image.open("/home/zeppelin/emask.png"))

stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)
stopwords.add("said")

wc = WordCloud(background_color="white", mask=emask,
               stopwords=stopwords, max_font_size = 100, relative_scaling=0.4)

# generate word cloud
wc.generate(text)

# store to file
#wc.to_file("/tmp/emask.png")

# show
# plot the WordCloud image                       
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 10), facecolor = None)
plt.imshow(wc)
plt.axis("off")
plt.tight_layout(pad = 0)
 
plt.show()
